result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael K Manning was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The Def is to obtain and maintain full time employment or enroll in a course of education or a combination of both.
.

Def is not to consume or possess any alcohol or controlled substances without a prescription from licensed physician, with random screenings.
.

Pay Crime Lab and Drug Assessment fee (see 'other' above for amount)

  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendent in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

  Pay DOC Supervision fees.

  Undergo any other assessments or evaluations deemed appropriate by PO and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Agent to look at behavioral health issues.

  The Court may grant you an early discharge following successful completion of the conditions of this court order, adherence to the rules of your supervision, and upon the recommendation of your agent.

Credit for 33 days if probation revoked.
